The paper discusses the nature of visualization design study, which involves the creation of visualizations to explore research questions. This falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the criteria for rigor in research, which is relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the subjective and socially constructed nature of knowledge, which is relevant to Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Computation and Language (cs.CL).
